<br>
You will soon be approaching that point where you will not want to be taunting mobs.  This is something to strongly consider when upgrading your weapons and equipment.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, you would be better off obtaining a non-proc'ing weapon - the 10/23 sword you mentioned would be a better alternative to the dragon horn yak.  The ykesha proc can be a big taunt, as you get closer to 50 you'll realize why this isn't such a good idea.  The better ratio of the velious warsword will make your damage output more consistent overall.  That dragon horn yak won't proc every fight, but the ratio is there for every battle.<br>
<br>
I would not drop 4ac of the Tolan's Gauntlets for the stats of the Iksar scaled gloves.  AC is what will be keeping you alive, the additional few points of str, dex, and hp wouldn't be worth losing the 4 AC points.  (You can always get stat buffs from the group to give you those added str, dex, and hp bonuses.)  The clickable effect of the gauntlets will work at level 45 - but the longer casting time usually means you won't use it unless OOM.  There are very, very, few instances where I would sacrifice AC for stats.  Keep max AC in all available slots, and you'll be much more effective when taking hits.<br>
<br>
As a side note, you could be fighting in Skyshrine at your level... good exp around level 40 I believe.  The sentry armor which drops there is an upgrade for most pieces you are currently wearing.  The drawback is trashing your Dragon faction - but it will build your Giant faction.<br>
<br>
Good luck bro!<br>
<br>
-Borz<br>
