<br>
at 49, here's what i've got:<br>
<br>
Cougar claw earring: ac 4 3str 2dex.  cheap, you cant beat it for ac, or stats.<br>
<br>
Ry gorr neck: ac 9, 4 sta, a couple saves. Again, really cheap, great ac for a neck, and decent stats.<br>
<br>
Worked Dragon mask: ac 10, 8cha, 6sv fire.  Great ac, the cha isnt a necessity in the least bit, but it made me hit 100 cha, so I liked it. 6sv fire is a nice bonus.<br>
<br>
Tolans helm: ac 18, superior camo fx. Fantastic ac. 0 stats, and a spell you get at 49. cast time is horrific.<br>
<br>
Silver Glided something ear ring: ac 5, 20hp/20mana, saves, 5 charges of force. Easy n00b quest in LF. Great ac, and good stats.<br>
<br>
66hp/6ac rings. Cant beat the ac for fingers. 66hps is nothing to sneeze at either. Only problem with this is, the more tolans you get, the less stats you have, and you'll itch to find a good item or two to pick up some stats.<br>
<br>
Hero bracer: ac 9, 10str some saves. Another classic, easy to get, cheap to buy, standard.<br>
<br>
Tolans Gloves. Ac 14, fx snare. Long cast time, only real use i've found for it, is to pull, if you want to pull with snare. Nice for when you're camping something green that you dont want to run off, and you dont want to waste mana.  I'd go with Sentry gloves, the ac 12, 5dex/agil/saves pair, if you've got the 1500 or so to spend.<br>
<br>
Tolans Bracer. ac 14, fx summon arrows. No stats, but free arrows for all time!  3dmg ones at that. Cant beat this bracer, hands down, with snare and root, if your archery skill is high, you can solo just about anything you want to (within limits, you are a ranger after all =)<br>
<br>
Tolans arms. ac 18, stinging swarm. Good spell to pull with. Again, the cast time is a little less than nice, but nice arms. Another good arm is the sleeves of the ancients which come from a guy in FM, that you can solo at your level. they're something like ac 16 (14?) 5str and 8 char. Not sure on the stats really, but nice none the less.<br>
<br>
Sebilite Scale Coat. Ac 22, 6str 6wis, 6cha. Great all around chestpiece for a wisdom casting class that can use it. You could go with Treeweave, ac 25, 10str, of course, but i prefer the multi stat bonus in this case.<br>
<br>
Crested spaulders. ac 11, 6sta. There are better mantles out there. The dragon ones that are out now are really nice. ac 13, 35hp/35 mana, and up. Outside of those though, there's not really much to choose from. Obulous death shroud is nice, but 1 less ac, and not really worth the 7k you'll dish out for one.<br>
<br>
Tigeraptor cloak. The cloak for rangers. Simply put. If you can find a tailor that can make you one of these, do it. Stats are similar to this: (so many stats on this one, i really cant remember offhand what's exact)  Ac 9, 8str, 7sta, 6wis, 8 dex, 6agil. Good ac. there's better ac cloaks out there, for sure, but statwise, you won't beat this one.<br>
<br>
TBB. ac 8, 15str. here's my extra str. Would rather have another belt, but havnt really found one I want yet. Spider fur, after the patch looks  nice.<br>
<br>
petrified bark leggings. Ac 18, 10sta, 20 mana, ranger only. Great ac, good stats, ranger only.<br>
<br>
Lodizal boots. ac 14, 7str, and turtle skin effect, which is a 10ac buff. Works at lvl 10+, and can be cast on others. Kind of an ugly boot =), but until i get some tolans, they'll do.<br>
<br>
Weapons:<br>
<br>
/sigh, i've tried so many different combos, its sad. the best combo i've tried that i like is this: Revultant whip in main.  5/14 5dex 4agil (PoH dropped), and Green Jade Axe (17/34, tons of stats, one of which is NEG 15sta). In short, a low dmg, low dly mainhand, and a high dmg/whatever dly in off.  But, that's just me.<br>
<br>
Raincaller Bow. Till you can get one of the newer Velium bows, i'd try to  pick one of these up. quest can be done at your level in a group, i still use mine, and i love it. 21/40 7str/7dex, 5 charges of spirit strike.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's my 2 cents worth. this is what i wear, and i'd suggest most of it to you, unless otherwise noted, and by no means does this mean that i think you've made bad choices if you dont agree, to each his own =)<br>
<br>
<br>
Seprentor Nevermore<br>
Coven of Lore<br>
49th archer<br>
